Suggests: jackd2 | pipewire-jack
Description: low-latency scsynth-compatible audio synthesis server
 SuperSonic is a port of SuperCollider's scsynth audio engine focused on
 low latency and long-session reliability. The server accepts scsynth
 command-line flags and the scsynth OSC command set, so SuperCollider
 clients (such as Sonic Pi) can launch and drive it as a drop-in
 replacement for scsynth.
 .
 Ableton Link session sync (including Link Audio streaming), MIDI I/O,
 game controller input, and OSC cue networking are built in. Commands
 arrive as OSC over UDP by default; TCP, Unix-socket, and shared-memory
 command transports are also available.
